1
00:00:00,087 --> 00:00:07,050
JavaScript classes are primarily syntactic sugar over JavaScript's existing prototype-based inheritance

2
00:00:07,438 --> 00:00:15,675
They provide a clearer and more recognizable syntax for object-oriented programming that is familiar to developers from other languages

3
00:00:16,075 --> 00:00:18,387
JavaScript classes can contain properties

4
00:00:18,625 --> 00:00:19,387
methods

5
00:00:19,550 --> 00:00:20,400
constructors

6
00:00:20,587 --> 00:00:21,625
and static methods

7
00:00:21,988 --> 00:00:26,188
offering a more structured way to create and manage objects and their behaviors

